properties.description: A small spring drains into a beck which cuts off the lower corner of the field. Both water off the lower corner of the field. Both water courses carry generous amount of Chrysosplenium oppositifilium, Veronica beccabunga and Caltha palustris.
properties.species: Chrysosplenium oppositifilium, Veronica beccabunga and Caltha palustris.

properties.species: Chrysosplenium oppositifilium, Veronica beccabunga and Caltha palustris.
Silene flos-cuculi, Dactilorhiza fuchsii, Hydrocotyle vulgaris, Alchillea ptarmica, Veronica beccabunga, Lotus corniculatus, Galium palustre and Epilobium palustre.
properties.description: A small beck draining from Great Mell Fell plus two other small flushes have produced an area of marshy grassland dominated by Juncus and Cirsium

A belt of well-established broadleaved plantation edging a large field of pasture, principally Fagus sylvatica and Acer pseudoplatanus. Also Betula pendula and a single Quercus of an uncommon species.
properties.species: Fagus sylvatica and Acer pseudoplatanus. Also Betula pendula and a single Quercus of an uncommon species.

properties.description: Flat area by beck forms valley mire, fed by surrounding flushes. By stream, probably subject to occasional inundations. (Carex paniculata, Sphagnum spp., Menyanthes trifoliata, Comarum palustre).
properties.species: Also present: Silene flos-cuculi, Caltha palustris, Hydrocotyle vulgaris, Epilobium palustre, Lotus pedunculatus, Galium palustre, Mentha aquatica, Myosotis scorpioides, Valeriana officinalis, Oenanthe sp., Equisetum fluviatile, Angelica sylvestris

properties.description: A diverse community of plants in and on the margins of the beck, including Phalaris arundinacea, Equisetum fluviatile, Typha latifolia, Mentha aquatica, Carex rostrata and Lythrum salicaria.
properties.species: Phalaris arundinacea, Equisetum fluviatile, Typha latifolia, Mentha aquatica, Carex rostrata and Lythrum salicaria.
Corylus avellana, Fraxinus excelsior, Sorbus aucuparia, Crataegus monogyna, Salix sp, Betula sp and Malus sylvestris.
properties.description: Semi-natural broadleaved woodland on steep stream gill sides; stock-grazed with poor ground flora and little regeneration.
